      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "se utiliza bastante similar al otro manualmap #»「✋」manual-map , solo que este deja menos logs y lo recomiendo mucho mas\n\nabren el manualmap, nombre del dll, proceso al que quieren injectar y luego ruta completa del dll\n\n\n\nPath to the manualmap.exe (adjust if different)\n$exePath = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\ManualMap.exe\"\n\nArguments for the program: dllName, processName, and dllPath (adjust with real values)\n$dllName = \"DLLIMPORT\"  # Name of the injection DLLIMPORT\n$processName = \"PROCESSNAME\"  # Name of the target process\n$dllPath = \"PATHDLL\"  # Full path to the DLL to inject\n\nif (-not (Test-Path $exePath)) {\n    exit\n}\n\nif (-not (Test-Path $dllPath)) {\n    exit\n}\n\n$bytes = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($exePath)\n$asm = [System.Reflection.Assembly]::Load($bytes)\n$argsArray = [string[]] @($dllName, $processName, $dllPath)\n$asm.EntryPoint.Invoke($null, (, $argsArray))",
